Seems like need to rebase due to my PR merged...
I have rebased.

So...if input list like this
```
"Inputs": [
    "DIMM [A-L][1-2] CPU0"
],
```

I can add a "MissingIsAcceptable" list in the same pid config like
```
"MissingIsAcceptable": [
    "DIMM A[1-2] CPU0"
],
```

And pid will not go into failsafe mode when DIMM_A1_CPU0 or DIMM_A2_CPU0 sensor reading is na?

Does `entity-manager` allow regular expressions these days? In `phosphor-pid-control` it is all received as ordinary strings.

The strings must be an exact match. So, it will depend on what substitutions `entity-manager` does. The string in `Inputs` must equal the string in `MissingIsAcceptable` after all substitutions have been resolved, in order for this input to be acceptable to go missing.

In phosphor-pid-control, [findSensors](https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-pid-control/blob/master/dbus/dbusutil.cpp#L77-L91) function supports regular expressions, so [Inputs and Outputs](https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-pid-control/blob/master/dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp#L694-L703) string can use regular expression.
I think MissingIsAcceptable can also change to use this function?

example "Inputs" in my machine =>
```
busctl introspect xyz.openbmc_project.EntityManager /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/board/izumiEMR/DIMM_CPU0_PID
.Inputs                               property  as        2 "DIMM[0-9]" "DIMM1[0-5]" emits-change writable

swampd[3989]: PID name: DIMM_CPU0_PID
swampd[3989]: inputs: DIMM11,
```
Hmm, you have a point. `TempToMargin` and `MissingIsAcceptable` will both benefit from regular expression expansion. I will have to rework this change to add that feature, if it is a requirement.

I took another look, and figured out how to make MissingIsAcceptable do the same parsing as Inputs. Now, both of these lists of strings should be treated the same way, expanded by regex, so matching-up should now work.
Giving myself +2 because somebody else gave +1
